<section xml:id="loops_vocabulary"
         xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Vocabulary</title>
  <p>
    <dl>
      <li>
        <title>loop:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>loop</h>
          </idx> A statement that executes a sequence of statements
          repeatedly.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>loop body:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>loop body</h>
          </idx> The statements inside the loop.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>infinite loop:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>infinite loop</h>
          </idx> A loop whose condition is always true.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>increment:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>increment</h>
          </idx> Increase the value of a variable.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>decrement:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>decrement</h>
          </idx> Decrease the value of a variable.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>iteration:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>iteration</h>
          </idx> Executing a sequence of statements repeatedly.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>loop variable:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>loop variable</h>
          </idx> A variable that is initialized, tested, and updated
          in order to control a loop.</p>
      </li>
    </dl>
  </p>
</section>